# Case Study: 6688 – Prevent Invalid Database Query Exceptions from Being Reported During Report Generation

## Context

This case study analyzes a production defect where **invalid report configuration properties**
(e.g., spaces, special characters, or unexpected field names) caused **database query exceptions**
during report generation.

Although the system already displayed an error to the user and prevented report download,
these **expected, user-caused errors were also being reported to the monitoring system**,
creating unnecessary alert noise.

